		<body>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><date>Jay 5 &#47; 53</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I beg to acknowledge<lb/> Recpt of your Esteed note of the <date>29th</date> ult<lb/> particularly note the contents</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I beg to say try no&#44; as you well<lb/> know&#44; I have not only a large family<lb/> but sisters &#38; aunt to support and<lb/> the claims upon me are heavy<lb/> I therefore regret I cannot<lb/> comply unto your request to<lb/> grant a pension of &#36;200 or &#36;300<lb/> p year to <persName>Miss Judah</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I spake with <persName>Mr David Judah</persName><lb/> the last time I was in <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> relative to <persName>Miss Judah</persName>&#58; he is a simple<lb/> man&#44; but himself to support &#38; <add>&#63;</add><lb/> I believe has extend relief to her&#44;<lb/> and I can hardly think she is<lb/> in such great distress as you<lb/> apprehend</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Your friend &#38; se</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">M C Mordecai</persName></p>
		</body>
